      <section>
        <title>Expected only a small fall in EU debt to 2020</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>
            Rating agency Moody’s said the eurozone sovereign's ratings will likely remain stable in 2016 but fading fiscal
            consolidation, limited progress on structural reforms, and rising political risks limit upside potential and create
            longer-term risks. Even as debt loads remain stubbornly high, the deleveraging process has been hampered by a combination
            of low growth and low inflation with progress on structural reforms limited at both a national and a eurozone level.
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>Europe 2020: 10 years bond profit</title>
          <paragraph>
            This data wants to illustrate situation of government bond 10 years profit in 2020; high profits of this bonds are surely
            good for investors, but isn’t good for governments, because they have to pay more interests; so high profits = more risk.
