      <section>
        <title>Well, that didn’t work</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>
            The BoJ and ECB recently launched some measures for currency devaluation in the sense
            that money printing and lower interest rates generally cause the offending country currency,
            sending its exchange rate down versus those of its trading partners. Well, that didn’t work.
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>Expectation vs Reality</title>
          <paragraph>
            This was what they were hoping for: weaker currencies to boost their export and make their
            insanely-large debt more manageable. Instead, they both have popped versus the dollar, which
            means exports have gotten more expensive and both systems debt loads are now harder to manage.
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
